Design-system rules for UI work in __APP_NAME__. See AGENTS.md for the full doctrine.

- Build UI from `@cooud-ui/ui` components. Do not re-implement a primitive that already exists there.
- Prefer `npx cooud-ui add <slug>` to scaffold a component or block before hand-rolling one. Own only the parts you actually need to customize.
- Theme through tokens. Read colors, spacing, radius, and typography from `@cooud-ui/tokens` (or their CSS variables) and switch themes via `useTheme`.
- Never inline raw colors. No hardcoded hex, `rgb()`, `hsl()`, or named colors in components or styles — reference a token.
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. Gate non-essential animation and provide a reduced-motion path.
- Keep components accessible and controlled: semantic roles, keyboard support, and no unbounded effects or polling in render.
